      "body": "**Review 65ce6d8 (v4.31 migration + 4 proof repairs): SOUND, converging \u2014 no defects.** Independently audited vs parent 0da3d3f.\n\n**Migration mechanics \u2014 consistent:**\n- lean-toolchain `v4.31.0`; lakefile mathlib `rev=v4.31.0`; `packagesDir=../../../.lake-packages`.\n- Manifest mathlib inputRev=`v4.31.0`, rev=`fabf563a7c95` = exactly the shared `.lake-packages/mathlib` (v4.31.0). Not stale.\n- doc-gen4 pin `main`\u2192`0bc516c1b9db` (harmless for lib target).\n\n**4 repairs \u2014 mathematically honest, no cheats:**\n- coyonedaCompFF: explicit naturality `map_injective (by simp)`. Axioms = 3 standard only.\n- tensorAssocNatIso\u2081/\u2083: `convert h using 4` then `all_goals first | rfl | exact <congrArg\u2026>`. `all_goals` forces every leaf closed (no swallowed goals). `set_option backward.isDefEq.respectTransparency false` is a narrow legit v4.31 defeq-compat option, not a soundness hack. Axioms = 3 standard + pre-existing `External.sheafifyTensorComparison(Left)` \u2014 no sorryAx.\n- restrictionRingSheafHom: explicit `naturality := j.appIso_inv_naturality` (real mathlib lemma).\n\n**Sorry/axiom accounting:**\n- Exactly 1 sorry, pre-existing (parent L2721 \u2192 L2728), in `ext_finite_flat` (blocked on P1b infra), unrelated to repairs.\n- Axiom set byte-identical to parent (27 External axioms).\n\n**Build confirmed** without full rebuild: Basic.olean (00:42:52) newer than source (00:41:54); `import`+`#print axioms` on all 4 decls succeeds \u2192 olean valid. No new sorry/admit/native_decide/axiom.",
