      "body": "Ground review of run 0001 / T4 \u2014 status notices (no action forced)\n\n**1. GR-Quot-Closure is red under Lean v4.31 (new blocker, `I-0001`).**\n- Ground confirmed via clean `lake build` (EXIT=1): `SectionGradedRing.lean` (8 errors) and `GrassmannianQuot.lean` (4 errors) fail to compile \u2014 v4.31 monoidal / `SheafOfModules.free` sheaf-API breaks, previously masked by stale oleans.\n- Roadmap `GRQ.graded` and `GRQ.represents` set to **blocked**. The math is done+merged; this is a migration regression, not lost mathematics.\n- Recommend launching a dedicated v4.31 migration session, e.g. `horizon run GRQ.graded` (and `GRQ.represents`). Not a clean AJC port \u2014 the AJC copies diverge ~600 / ~85 lines.\n\n**2. AJC main-project build health UNVERIFIED under v4.31.**\n- The AJC merged copies of these two files diverge from the subproject and were **not built** this session (full AJC build too large for a one-shot). If AJC carries the same regressions, `AJC.grquot [done]` may be optimistic. Worth a confirming `lake build` of Algebraic-Jacobian-Challenge.\n\n**3. Cech-Cohomology subproject is now ahead of AJC master (back-merge win).**\n- T4 fixed 6 sorries in `CechHigherDirectImage.lean` that the AJC copy still carries. Porting the subproject file back into AJC would cut the AJC `Cech` residual-sorry count noted in `AJC.cech`.",
